  "prompt": "Where do we get beef jerky or biltong in London?",
  "response": "In London, you can find beef jerky or biltong in various places, including:\n\n1. **Specialty Stores and Markets**:\n   - **The Jerky Group**: They offer a variety of beef jerky and other dried meat products.\n   - **Borough Market**: Known for its diverse food offerings, you can find vendors selling beef jerky and biltong.\n   - **Camden Market**: Another popular spot for unique food items including beef jerky and biltong.\n\n2. **Supermarkets and Grocery Stores**:\n   - **Tesco**, **Sainsbury's**, **Waitrose**, and **Morrisons** often carry packaged beef jerky and biltong in their snack sections.\n   - **Whole Foods Market**: Known for its organic and specialty foods, Whole Foods often stocks high-quality beef jerky and biltong.\n\n3. **Online Retailers**:\n   - **Amazon**: Offers a wide variety of beef jerky and biltong brands.\n   - **The British Biltong Company**: A specialized online retailer with a good selection of biltong.\n   - **Graze**: A subscription service that offers snacks, including beef jerky.\n\n4. **Specialty Butcher Shops**:\n   - **The Ginger Pig**: A renowned butcher shop with several locations in London.\n   - **C Lidgate**: A high-quality butcher shop in Holland Park.\n\n5. **International Food Stores**:\n   - **The South African Shop**: Located in Wimbledon, it specializes in South African products including biltong.\n\nThese locations provide a variety of options for purchasing beef jerky and biltong, catering to different tastes and preferences.",
